 A 21-year-old university student was on Monday arraigned in connection with the murder of a 38-year-old
woman in Molo, Nakuru County. Mark Njoroge Wanjiku, who is a
Third Year Computer Science student at Kibabii University, was presented before Molo Resident Magistrate Rhoda Yato. Njoroge was arrested on Sunday, January 9 in Lanet, Nakuru after Mary Njeri Kamau's decomposing and mutilated
body was found in the house he was living in. It was reported that Mary Njeri, a mother of
eight, went missing after leaving her home on 31st December 2021. According to detectives, Njorge failed to explain to
detectives why a dead mutilated body was
found in his house upon questioning. Appearing before Molo Resident Magistrate Rhoda Yator, the
investigating officer made an application to hold the suspect
for another 14 to conclude investigations. Magistrate Yator
granted the application.  The case will be mentioned on the 24th of January 2022.